5
00:00:30,820 --> 00:00:35,060
=Way To You=

6
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:36,380
(Highlights)
It is Chinese New Year today.

7
00:00:36,380 --> 00:00:37,640
So we're preparing the reunion dinner.

8
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:38,220
OK.

9
00:00:38,220 --> 00:00:38,930
Yeah.

10
00:00:38,930 --> 00:00:40,300
It's so easy.

11
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:41,930
Here comes hot-pot.

12
00:00:44,260 --> 00:00:44,940
Great!

13
00:00:46,910 --> 00:00:49,900
Happy Chinese New Year.

14
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:50,920
(New Mentor: Krist)

15
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:53,240
Alright, let's enjoy
this happy moment together.

16
00:00:53,240 --> 00:00:54,470
I don't dare to watch.

17
00:00:54,470 --> 00:00:55,680
Why are you still standing there? Go!

18
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:56,550
Why are you yelling at him?

19
00:00:56,550 --> 00:00:57,940
Is that all you know how to say?

20
00:00:57,940 --> 00:00:59,170
Then I've got nothing to say.

21
00:00:59,170 --> 00:01:00,250
You betrayed my trust!

22
00:01:00,850 --> 00:01:02,760
You stepped on me
and still have the nerve to talk back?

23
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:08,080
(Filming Day)

24
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:12,100
Three, two, one, action!

25
00:01:12,630 --> 00:01:13,670
Why did you step on me?

26
00:01:15,070 --> 00:01:17,800
So what if I did?
Can't you just deal with it?

27
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:19,000
But you stepped on me!

28
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,310
What now? I can't say anything about it?

29
00:01:21,420 --> 00:01:22,230
Wait.

30
00:01:22,230 --> 00:01:25,240
Why are you yelling at her?
She didn't do anything wrong.

31
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:26,040
Hey!

32
00:01:27,570 --> 00:01:29,060
Y ou've gained weight, kid.

33
00:01:29,190 --> 00:01:31,860
I'm... a polite ghost.

34
00:01:31,950 --> 00:01:34,320
What do you mean "polite"?
I'm taking a shower!

35
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:39,040
It's been three months already,
and you're the only one who can see me.

36
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:47,590
What gives you the right to treat Lin
like that? Don't go too far.

37
00:01:47,590 --> 00:01:49,600
President Gu,
what kind of person do you think I am?

38
00:01:51,190 --> 00:01:54,210
President Gu! President Gu!

39
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:57,760
(It's finally performance time)

40
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:22,080
(Which mysterious guest
will appear this time?)

41
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:23,320
Hello, everyone.

42
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:24,010
Hello.

43
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:26,270
I'm so nervous.

44
00:02:28,060 --> 00:02:29,720
Nice to meet you all.

45
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:30,750
Nice to meet you.

46
00:02:30,970 --> 00:02:31,970
(Krist Perawat Sangpotirat)
(Thai, 30yo, Actor/Singer)

47
00:02:31,970 --> 00:02:33,380
(Works: SOTUS 1&2, Our Skyy
The Ex-Morning, Love Beyond Frontier)

48
00:02:33,380 --> 00:02:33,980
(Mint to Be, Good Old Days)

49
00:02:43,230 --> 00:02:46,110
Sorry, I didn't hear clearly.
Could you say that again?

50
00:02:46,110 --> 00:02:53,560
I'm here today
to watch your drama performances.

51
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,240
Let's start with introductions.

52
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,830
Hello everyone, I'm Krist.

53
00:02:55,830 --> 00:02:57,880
Hello.

54
00:02:57,890 --> 00:03:00,010
Hello.

55
00:03:00,010 --> 00:03:05,940
I heard some of you
have never acted before.

56
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:07,420
(Awkward)

57
00:03:07,420 --> 00:03:09,360
Is this your first time?

58
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:10,470
Yes.

59
00:03:10,470 --> 00:03:11,340
(Awkward)

60
00:03:11,340 --> 00:03:14,140
I snuck a peak.

61
00:03:17,810 --> 00:03:19,650
You're all really good.

62
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:21,630
(Ready? Let's go.)

63
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:24,130
Alright, let's enjoy this together.

64
00:03:24,130 --> 00:03:24,740
Let's watch.

65
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:27,520
This is so awkward.
I don't dare to watch.

66
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:29,840
I'm so nervous.

67
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:31,170
(Starring: Cannon & Pippin)
(Galaxy Garden)

68
00:03:31,170 --> 00:03:32,300
What?

69
00:03:32,350 --> 00:03:35,470
(Got dragged into the drama myself.)

70
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:37,640
(Looking forward)

71
00:03:37,710 --> 00:03:38,540
Cannon.

72
00:03:41,390 --> 00:03:42,860
Now I'm nervous too.

73
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:44,950
(Don't dare to watch)

74
00:03:57,180 --> 00:03:59,600
(Pippin appears as a girl
for the first time)

75
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:07,200
Are you crazy? What are you doing here?

76
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:10,510
Now you care about me?

77
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,770
Stop talking.
Just come upstairs with me first.

78
00:04:15,070 --> 00:04:16,110
Just leave me alone.

79
00:04:20,410 --> 00:04:22,290
Oh my gosh what is this?

80
00:04:23,170 --> 00:04:24,680
Whoa this is pro!

81
00:04:27,940 --> 00:04:29,380
Didn't you say
you didn't want to see me?

82
00:04:31,420 --> 00:04:32,610
Daoming Wu,

83
00:04:32,810 --> 00:04:34,430
what do you want actually?

84
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:35,700
I don't have your number.

85
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:37,120
And I don't know what time you'd come.

86
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,230
I've been here

87
00:04:39,230 --> 00:04:40,460
waiting for four hours.

88
00:04:44,460 --> 00:04:45,290
Alright.

89
00:04:45,940 --> 00:04:47,370
This time, it's my fault.

90
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:48,730
I'm sorry.

91
00:04:49,030 --> 00:04:51,400
How about I take you out for a meal?

92
00:04:56,650 --> 00:04:57,380
Fine, let's go.

93
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:05,300
It's not over yet.

94
00:05:06,980 --> 00:05:08,080
My heart's fluttering.

95
00:05:08,470 --> 00:05:09,180
Baicai,

96
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,080
can you dance?

97
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:15,510
Dance what?

98
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:20,980
Waltz.

99
00:05:23,850 --> 00:05:25,180
Why are they suddenly dancing?

100
00:05:25,180 --> 00:05:26,880
This is so random.

101
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:29,520
But I don't know how.

102
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,010
I'll teach you.

103
00:05:39,490 --> 00:05:41,360
Why dance all of a sudden?

104
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:43,400
I just feel like it.

105
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:44,010
And also because,

106
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:47,350
there's a piano here too.

107
00:05:48,940 --> 00:05:50,140
And I also...

108
00:05:55,910 --> 00:05:57,850
But it's okay if you don't want to.

109
00:05:59,670 --> 00:06:02,360
Alright then.

110
00:06:05,260 --> 00:06:07,120
(They're into it)

111
00:06:09,670 --> 00:06:11,080
Are they really dancing now?

112
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:27,000
Let me escape please...

113
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:33,840
Put your hand on my shoulder.

114
00:06:36,890 --> 00:06:37,630
Oh...

115
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:39,740
I don't dare to watch.

116
00:06:52,490 --> 00:06:53,470
Why did you step on me?

117
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:57,720
So what if I did? Just deal with it.

118
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,480
Do you have to make such a big deal?

119
00:06:59,660 --> 00:07:00,660
He's mad.

120
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:02,750
You stepped on me
and still have the nerve to talk back?

121
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:03,850
The nerve to talk back?

122
00:07:03,850 --> 00:07:05,360
Is that all you know how to say?

123
00:07:05,710 --> 00:07:07,690
You're nothing but an idiot!

124
00:07:08,690 --> 00:07:10,770
How many times
have you called me that today?

125
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:12,190
Say it again. I dare you.

126
00:07:12,460 --> 00:07:13,020
Idiot.

127
00:07:13,020 --> 00:07:14,060
You're an idiot!

128
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:18,800
(Wanna find more interesting
stage live broadcast?)

129
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:21,160
(Follow @waytoyou2026 on Tiktok.
You'll get more surpring contents.)

130
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,490
That was great!

131
00:07:23,830 --> 00:07:25,520
(Can't watch)

132
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:27,210
(They can't even look at each other)

133
00:07:27,210 --> 00:07:28,920
Pippin, I'd like to ask.

134
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:29,900
Or should I ask,

135
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:31,550
(Why dress as a girl?)
why wear a wig

136
00:07:31,550 --> 00:07:34,490
(Why dress as a girl?)
and take the role as a girl?

137
00:07:34,490 --> 00:07:36,900
Well, in this script,

138
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:39,020
the character is a girl.

139
00:07:39,020 --> 00:07:40,280
And before this,

140
00:07:40,280 --> 00:07:43,500
I never had the chance
to play a female role.

141
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:45,520
(Brand new experience)
So for me,

142
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:48,130
(Brand new experience)
this is an interesting experience

143
00:07:48,130 --> 00:07:50,250
to try playing a girl.

144
00:07:50,250 --> 00:07:52,250
I think it's very special.

145
00:07:52,250 --> 00:07:53,450
I find it interesting.

146
00:07:53,450 --> 00:07:54,360
Very good.

147
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:55,160
Because

148
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:58,560
an actor's job is to play roles.

149
00:07:58,560 --> 00:08:00,040
Any role,

150
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:02,960
as long as we feel comfortable,
enjoy it, and find it interesting.

151
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:04,280
I can feel

152
00:08:04,420 --> 00:08:06,560
that he really enjoyed performing.

153
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,800
His expressions

154
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:12,380
and his feminine gestures
were convincing.

155
00:08:12,620 --> 00:08:15,360
What he presented felt convincing.

156
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:20,170
(Surprise)

157
00:08:20,170 --> 00:08:21,760
During that romantic scene,

158
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:25,530
the way you conveyed emotions
through eye contact while dancing,

159
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:29,120
I was smiling the whole time.

160
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,960
(Happy) Really?

161
00:08:33,040 --> 00:08:34,100
Well done.

162
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:35,180
(Praise)

163
00:08:35,180 --> 00:08:36,070
You were amazing too.

164
00:08:36,070 --> 00:08:37,790
You were really, really good.

165
00:08:37,790 --> 00:08:40,580
(Encouraging each other)

166
00:08:40,580 --> 00:08:42,920
(Starring: Eugene Tron)
(Galaxy Garden)

167
00:08:43,650 --> 00:08:47,120
(Can't even open his eyes)

168
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,230
So it's this pair now.

169
00:08:58,300 --> 00:09:00,140
The rain looks so real.

170
00:09:02,390 --> 00:09:04,040
Young Master, please take my umbrella.

171
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:05,340
The rain's really heavy.

172
00:09:05,580 --> 00:09:07,970
What's it to you? Just go.

173
00:09:10,370 --> 00:09:10,990
Go away.

174
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,080
He's arrived.

175
00:09:20,380 --> 00:09:21,720
Daoming Wu? What are you doing here?

176
00:09:22,230 --> 00:09:23,100
Are you crazy?

177
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,550
So cute. He's even wearing a hairpin.

178
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:26,720
Come on, come upstairs with me.

179
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:28,050
I don't need you.

180
00:09:35,270 --> 00:09:37,020
Didn't you say you didn't want
to see me?

181
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:40,140
Daoming Wu, what exactly do you want?

182
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:43,790
I don't have your number.

183
00:09:45,310 --> 00:09:47,170
And I didn't know when you'd come.

184
00:09:48,970 --> 00:09:50,510
So I just waited here.

185
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:53,140
Alright... this time, it's my fault.

186
00:09:53,290 --> 00:09:53,980
Sorry.

187
00:09:54,220 --> 00:09:55,690
Let me treat you to a meal then.

188
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,030
Okay?

189
00:09:58,990 --> 00:09:59,770
Let's go.

190
00:10:01,820 --> 00:10:03,240
Okay fine. I'm freezing to death.

191
00:10:06,010 --> 00:10:07,740
A lamb and a big bad wolf.

192
00:10:08,980 --> 00:10:09,820
Do you know how to dance?

193
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,000
No.

194
00:10:12,350 --> 00:10:13,080
I'll teach you.

195
00:10:15,770 --> 00:10:16,350
Why?

196
00:10:19,290 --> 00:10:21,060
So you don't want to dance with me?

197
00:10:21,470 --> 00:10:22,200
Alright then.

198
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:26,680
Erm...

199
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:27,530
Okay then.

200
00:10:38,550 --> 00:10:40,150
Put your hand on my shoulder.

201
00:10:40,330 --> 00:10:40,870
Like this?

202
00:10:41,170 --> 00:10:41,790
Yes.

203
00:10:42,190 --> 00:10:42,660
Good.

204
00:10:43,420 --> 00:10:44,340
Nice chemistry.

205
00:10:44,340 --> 00:10:44,860
(Likes it)

206
00:10:44,860 --> 00:10:47,000
One, two, three.

207
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,050
(Smiles unconsciously)

208
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:50,320
One, two, three.

209
00:10:57,680 --> 00:11:00,420
So what if I stepped on you?
Can't you just deal with it?

210
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:02,220
Why did you shout so loud?

211
00:11:02,710 --> 00:11:06,870
You stepped on me
and I'm not even allowed to react?

212
00:11:08,370 --> 00:11:09,920
You deserve a good beating.

213
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:11,380
A good beating?

214
00:11:11,380 --> 00:11:12,650
All you do is insult people.

215
00:11:14,170 --> 00:11:15,330
Like an idiot.

216
00:11:15,820 --> 00:11:17,250
Are you calling me an idiot?

217
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:18,050
Yeah.

218
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:24,040
Say that again, I dare you.

219
00:11:25,140 --> 00:11:26,520
Idiot.

220
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:28,000
You're an idiot.

221
00:11:30,150 --> 00:11:31,580
Don't think I won't get mad.

222
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,070
Then get mad.

223
00:11:33,690 --> 00:11:35,380
You're still an idiot anyway.

224
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:39,000
What are you looking at?

225
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:43,430
Enjoying watching me get scolded?

226
00:11:45,380 --> 00:11:46,750
Why are you still standing there? Scram!

227
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:50,020
So pitiful.

228
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:52,790
(Poor Deaw)

229
00:11:55,710 --> 00:11:56,510
A bit of resentment there.

230
00:11:56,510 --> 00:11:58,330
Yeah, definitely some resentment.

231
00:11:59,230 --> 00:12:01,250
(The most pitiful side character ever)
Poor him.

232
00:12:01,590 --> 00:12:03,180
He works as a servant

233
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:04,510
(Saying what everyone's thinking)
and still gets kicked out in the end.

234
00:12:07,220 --> 00:12:09,760
Why are you yelling at him?
He didn't do anything.

235
00:12:10,950 --> 00:12:12,090
He was interrupting us.

236
00:12:12,090 --> 00:12:13,530
I just sent him away.

237
00:12:15,290 --> 00:12:16,870
Did you see the way he looked at us?

238
00:12:20,390 --> 00:12:21,760
Then I've got nothing to say.

239
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:32,080
(Wanna find more interesting
stage live broadcast?)

240
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,920
(Follow @waytoyou2026 on Tiktok.
You'll get more surpring contents.)

241
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:35,400
The Daoming Wu I played

242
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,250
is a man of authority

243
00:12:36,250 --> 00:12:42,630
but doesn't know how to love.

244
00:12:42,630 --> 00:12:44,000
For my approach,

245
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:47,080
I tried to find something relatable.

246
00:12:47,410 --> 00:12:51,550
(Relatable)
things we think are right,

247
00:12:51,550 --> 00:12:53,690
but others might see as wrong.

248
00:12:53,690 --> 00:12:56,630
I used that emotional overlap

249
00:12:56,630 --> 00:12:58,220
to shape the performance.

250
00:12:58,450 --> 00:12:59,630
I can feel that your

251
00:13:00,140 --> 00:13:01,870
interpretation of this scene

252
00:13:01,870 --> 00:13:03,900
is very different from the first group.

253
00:13:04,460 --> 00:13:06,380
(A different perspective
from Pippin & Cannon)

254
00:13:06,380 --> 00:13:06,940
Tron

255
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:11,250
is willful,
but his performance goes deeper.

256
00:13:11,340 --> 00:13:12,900
(It draws you in)

257
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:16,870
It feels very realistic.

258
00:13:16,870 --> 00:13:19,990
It made the character feel alive.

259
00:13:19,990 --> 00:13:22,280
(Proud)

260
00:13:22,790 --> 00:13:25,160
To me,

261
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:27,480
this character looks
like a total villain.

262
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:30,640
I like actors who don't rush.

263
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:31,700
He builds it up slowly.

264
00:13:31,700 --> 00:13:33,880
If he hasn't found the feeling yet,

265
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:35,790
he'll build it up gradually,

266
00:13:35,790 --> 00:13:37,140
raising the emotion step by step.

267
00:13:37,140 --> 00:13:39,030
If he keeps performing often,

268
00:13:39,030 --> 00:13:41,080
(A promising actor)
his acting will definitely improve a lot.

269
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:43,920
When I watched this pair,

270
00:13:44,160 --> 00:13:44,760
I actually believe

271
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:46,700
(A loving CP)
the chemistry between them.

272
00:13:47,390 --> 00:13:48,900
Not just "kind of",

273
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:49,580
but I truly believe it.

274
00:13:49,580 --> 00:13:52,380
They conveyed everything
through their eyes.

275
00:13:52,380 --> 00:13:54,720
You can tell Tron is secretly in love.

276
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:58,820
As for Eugene,

277
00:13:59,180 --> 00:14:04,420
his eye acting could go further.

278
00:14:04,590 --> 00:14:05,910
(Needs stronger eye acting)
I could feel it,

279
00:14:05,910 --> 00:14:08,180
